cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.AI 

This paper deals with video content segmentation using visual features and a generative network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses an LSTM-based network, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. Additionally, the paper deals with a large dataset, which could place it in the cs.MM (Multimedia) category. The paper also deals with indexing and retrieval, which could place it in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) category. Finally, the paper uses unsupervised methods, which could place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category.
